SUMMARY:Macroeconomics – Shang-Jin Wei (Columbia) – Tolls on Entreprene
 urs from Capital Market Distortions: Evidence from IPO Locational Choices
LOCATION:Room 404\, FBE Building\, 111 Barry St\, Carlton VIC 3053
DESCRIPTION:Shang-Jin Wei: “Tolls on Entrepreneurs from Capital Market Di
 stortions: Evidence from IPO Locational Choices”\nhttps://business.colum
 bia.edu/faculty/people/shang-jin-wei\n\nZoom: https://unimelb.zoom.us/j/84
 055677057?pwd=q1KyfcUkOWfMfEThCYsc9fs2jh2vCa.1&from=addon\n\nGoogle Maps: 
 https://maps.app.goo.gl/BirLkJKurX9pSbBB8\n\nABSTRACT:\nCapital controls a
 nd other policy distortions in the capital market are costly to entreprene
 urs. We propose a structural estimation approach to quantify the effect us
 ing IPO locational choices. We estimate the willingness-to-pay to bypass t
 hese distortions by the Chinese entrepreneurs with overseas listed firms t
 o be a haircut in firm value by 50-60%. We infer that the welfare for the 
 entrepreneurs could rise by 22% from the relevant capital market reforms.
URL:https://unimelb.zoom.us/j/84055677057?pwd=q1KyfcUkOWfMfEThCYsc9fs2jh2vC
 a.1&from=addon
END:VEVENT
