SUMMARY:PhD Brown Bag Seminar – Jinjing Chen (University of Melbourne) 
 – Air Pollution and Road Safety: The Role of Agricultural Burning in Pak
 istan
LOCATION:Room 304\, FBE Building\, 111 Barry St\, Carlton VIC 3053
DESCRIPTION:Jinjing Chen: “Air Pollution and Road Safety: The Role of Agr
 icultural Burning in Pakistan”\n\nGoogle Maps: https://maps.app.goo.gl/B
 irLkJKurX9pSbBB8\n\nABSTRACT:\nRoad traffic accidents impose substantial s
 ocial costs\, especially in low- and middle-income countries\, yet the env
 ironmental determinants of accident risk remain poorly understood. Using a
 dministrative emergency accident records\, this paper studies the effect o
 f agricultural burning on road accidents in Punjab\, Pakistan\, from 2022 
 to 2025. I combine VIIRS active-fire detections with HYSPLIT-simulated smo
 ke plume trajectories to predict whether smoke from fires outside a local 
 area is transported into it\, and use this predicted smoke exposure as an 
 instrument for local smog exposure. I then use this variation to estimate 
 the causal effect of agricultural burning-related smoke on road accidents.
  In addition\, I  disentangle the roles of air pollution and reduced visib
 ility\, quantify the contribution of transboundary smoke from Indian Punja
 b\, and identify the upwind burn locations that generate the largest downs
 tream road-safety externalities\, with implications for spatially targeted
  enforcement.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cb72d21e53a175cbac85f93444d2c9d2@generated
DTSTAMP:20260422T200022Z
