SUMMARY:PhD Brown Bag Seminar – Kaiyue Chen (University of Melbourne) –
  Eﬀicient Allocation of Public Electric Vehicle Chargers
LOCATION:Room 304\, FBE Building\, 111 Barry St\, Carlton VIC 3053
DESCRIPTION:Kaiyue Chen: “Eﬀicient Allocation of Public Electric Vehicl
 e Chargers”\n\nGoogle Maps: https://maps.app.goo.gl/BirLkJKurX9pSbBB8\n\
 nABSTRACT:\nAs demand for electric vehicles (EVs) and public charging grow
 s\, efficiently allocating scarce charging capacity becomes increasingly i
 mportant. This paper examines alternative pricing mechanisms for allocatin
 g public Level 2 EV chargers to users with the highest marginal value. A t
 heoretical framework incorporates drivers’ heterogeneous willingness to 
 pay (WTP) and inconvenience costs of vacating\, and compares three mechani
 sms: flat electricity pricing\, flat pricing with an idle fee\, and flat p
 ricing with a spot occupancy fee.\n\nSimulations suggest that spot fees te
 nd to achieve higher welfare\, especially under high congestion\, by reall
 ocating charger access toward higher-WTP users and inducing earlier depart
 ures among users with lower vacate costs. These results are robust to exte
 nsions with charging-time limits and implementation frictions in departure
  timing. A field experiment is proposed to identify the causal effects of 
 pricing on behavior and to recover key structural parameters for counterfa
 ctual welfare analysis.
END:VEVENT
